# Why `inc[l] >= dec[r]` Works

```
l----------------------r

Increasing from left

l------inc[l]

Decreasing from right

dec[r]------r
```

### Case 1

```
l----inc[l]
      |
      |
dec[r]----r
```

They overlap.

A peak exists.

Mountain.

---

### Case 2

```
l---inc[l]


dec[r]------r
```

Gap exists.

That gap corresponds to a decrease followed by an increase.

Not Mountain.

